# Application
NODE_ENV=development
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ── Clerk Authentication ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get these from https://dashboard.clerk.com → your app → API Keys
#
# Setup steps:
# 1. Create a free Clerk account at https://clerk.com
# 2. Create a new application (choose "Email" as sign-in method)
# 3. Enable "Email verification code" strategy:
#    Dashboard → User & Authentication → Email, Phone, Username
#    → Email address → Verification → Email verification code
# 4. Copy the keys from API Keys page

NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=<your-clerk-publishable-key>
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=<your-clerk-secret-key>

# Clerk redirect URLs (match the app's route structure)
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/login
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/login
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL=/dashboard
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL=/dashboard

# ── External API (hosted backend) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# All API calls go to: https://zoho-backend-rho.vercel.app
# No local API routes are used — the backend is fully external.
#
# Backend note: The backend JWT middleware must be updated to verify Clerk JWTs.
# See: https://clerk.com/docs/backend-requests/handling/manual-jwt
